On Oct 21, 2005, at 10:31 AM, Wayne wrote:

> 1) Along with the taco plate and cover there are gaskets.  What  
> order are
> they to be installed in the motor?  Picture or drawing would be great.

The big red o-ring goes between the plate and the engine case. The  
ring paper gasket goes between the plate and it's cover but you'll  
find it's not really necessary.

> 2) Which way should the sender be pointed?  It looks like I have a  
> 50-50
> change of getting it right

Rearward.

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/MoreParts4/111-CoverPlate.jpg

> 3) The taco plate I got came with an old temp sender in place.   
> Does anyone
> know if this will work (& give correct readings) with the VDO gauge  
> sold on
> Bus Depot site?  Yes, I know you probably want the sender part  
> number - I'll
> get that soon.

They are often the longer style 400F senders from 914s. They don't  
work with the standard VDO gauges expecting a 300F sender. A new  
sender doesn't cost much.

